      <hedline>
        <hl1>Christine Miller Goes To Discovery.com</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By JANE L. LEVERE</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Christine Miller, executive vice president of Magazine Publishers of America, to take same post at Discovery.com (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Christine Miller said yesterday that she would leave the Magazine Publishers of America in New York, where she had been executive vice president and chief marketing officer, to take the same post at Discovery.com in Bethesda, Md., and New York, part of Discovery Communications.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Christine Miller said yesterday that she would leave the Magazine Publishers of America in New York, where she had been executive vice president and chief marketing officer, to take the same post at Discovery.com in Bethesda, Md., and New York, part of Discovery Communications.</p>
        <p>''This was an opportunity to go back to being a marketing executive with a brand,'' said Ms. Miller, 55, ''an important and powerful brand.'' Ms. Miller joined the magazine association in June 1997; her post at Discovery.com is new.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
